      "content": "i know there are people out there, but what's the point? they aren't her. it feels like every single version of a future where she isn't there is just... wrong. it's like a mistake. i've been staring at the wall for hours just thinking about how much easier it would be if i didn't have to wake up and face this void every single day. it feels like the only way to actually stop the hurting is to just not feel anything at all.",
